That said, it isn&#x27;t too hard to write re-usable helpers for promise based control flow, in a similar manner to what async.js does for callbacks.<p><pre><code>    function iff(condition, method) {
        return Promise.try(condition).then(result => {
            if (result) {
                return method();
            }
        });
    }

    function whilst(condition, method) {
        return iff(condition, () => {
            return Promise.try(method)
                .then(whilst.bind(null, condition, method));
        });
    }

    whilst(someAsyncAction, Promise.sleep.bind(null, 1000))
        .catch(err => {
            // ...
        })
</code></pre>
Naturally you wouldn&#x27;t want to re-implement all of this control flow every time you need it. But the end result is not too much boilerplate.
